msgstr "THEME AND CONTENTÂ Â "

msgid " Character's Ages."
msgstr " Character's Ages."

msgid ""
"The protagonist(s) of your story should be the same age as or a little older"
" than the reader. "
msgstr ""
"The protagonist(s) of your story should be the same age as or a little older"
" than the reader. "

msgid ""
"Establish the age of the protagonist as soon as possible, and make sure your"
" characters act appropriately for their ages."
msgstr ""
"Establish the age of the protagonist as soon as possible, and make sure your"
" characters act appropriately for their ages."

msgid " Taboos."
msgstr " Taboos."

msgid ""
"While the market is much more flexible than in the past, stay away from any "
"positive portrayal of drugs, tobacco, alcohol, explicit sex, crime, and "
"violence. "
msgstr ""
"While the market is much more flexible than in the past, stay away from any "
"positive portrayal of drugs, tobacco, alcohol, explicit sex, crime, and "
"violence. "

msgid ""
"Drunkenness particularly should never be portrayed in a humorous light. "
msgstr ""
"Drunkenness particularly should never be portrayed in a humorous light. "

msgid ""
"You will find certain themes, while not actually taboo, difficult to sell. "
msgstr ""
"You will find certain themes, while not actually taboo, difficult to sell. "

msgid ""
"Animals that talk to people are almost impossible to sellâ€”even as fantasy."
" "
msgstr ""
"Animals that talk to people are almost impossible to sellâ€”even as fantasy."
" "

msgid ""
"'Lil Toot and The Little Engine That Could aside, anthropomorphizing "
"inanimate objects also makes for a difficult sale. "
msgstr ""
"'Lil Toot and The Little Engine That Could aside, anthropomorphizing "
"inanimate objects also makes for a difficult sale. "

msgid ""
"Stories that turn out to be only a dream are not often welcome, especially "
"if waking up is used to solve a plot problem. "
msgstr ""
"Stories that turn out to be only a dream are not often welcome, especially "
"if waking up is used to solve a plot problem. "

msgid ""
"Things that are too cute, too old-fashioned, or too common usually get the "
"cold shoulder, too.Â "
msgstr ""
"Things that are too cute, too old-fashioned, or too common usually get the "
"cold shoulder, too.Â "

msgid "One of those not-taboo-but subjects is weight. "
msgstr "One of those not-taboo-but subjects is weight. "

msgid ""
"There is currently a medical, political, and social focus on overweight "
"children and youth that promises to have a very real impact on our culture. "
msgstr ""
"There is currently a medical, political, and social focus on overweight "
"children and youth that promises to have a very real impact on our culture. "

msgid ""
"At the same time, eating disorders are a very real issue, especially with "
"preteens and early teens. "
msgstr ""
"At the same time, eating disorders are a very real issue, especially with "
"preteens and early teens. "

msgid ""
"As a result, the subject of weight should be handled carefullyâ€”especially "
"if it is not the focus of the story or book you are writing."
msgstr ""
"As a result, the subject of weight should be handled carefullyâ€”especially "
"if it is not the focus of the story or book you are writing."

msgid " Fantasy and Fairy Stories."
msgstr " Fantasy and Fairy Stories."

msgid "Fantasy is a healthy field for juvenile publishing. "
msgstr "Fantasy is a healthy field for juvenile publishing. "

msgid ""
"However, retelling such classics as Thumbelina or The Goose Girl in modern "
"dress is sure to garner rejection slips instead of praise. "
msgstr ""
"However, retelling such classics as Thumbelina or The Goose Girl in modern "
"dress is sure to garner rejection slips instead of praise. "

msgid ""
"If you are tempted to begin your story \"Once upon a time,\" you should "
"probably think about how it will fit in your target publisher's list."
msgstr ""
"If you are tempted to begin your story \"Once upon a time,\" you should "
"probably think about how it will fit in your target publisher's list."

msgid " Mystery."
msgstr " Mystery."

msgid "There is a great difference between adult and children's mysteries. "
msgstr "There is a great difference between adult and children's mysteries. "

msgid "Violence is generally out for any age group. "
msgstr "Violence is generally out for any age group. "

msgid "For preteen readers, murder is out, and so are most dead bodies. "
msgstr "For preteen readers, murder is out, and so are most dead bodies. "

msgid ""
"The only corpses are generally ancient mummies that lend a creepy mood to a "
"story. "
msgstr ""
"The only corpses are generally ancient mummies that lend a creepy mood to a "
"story. "

msgid ""
"Missing treasure, old legends and secrets, theft, and even kidnapping have "
"formed the core of wonderful juvenile mysteries. "
msgstr ""
"Missing treasure, old legends and secrets, theft, and even kidnapping have "
"formed the core of wonderful juvenile mysteries. "

msgid ""
"Many mystery books are elaborate puzzles the reader is meant to solve.Â "
msgstr ""
"Many mystery books are elaborate puzzles the reader is meant to solve.Â "

msgid " Science Fiction."
msgstr " Science Fiction."

msgid ""
"Science fiction becomes popular around fourth or fifth grade when it is a "
"venue for fast-paced adventure. "
msgstr ""
"Science fiction becomes popular around fourth or fifth grade when it is a "
"venue for fast-paced adventure. "

msgid ""
"With science making headlines daily and subjects such as space and ecology "
"entering the standard curriculum by second or third grade, science fiction "
"stories may well find a home in even younger markets. "
msgstr ""
"With science making headlines daily and subjects such as space and ecology "
"entering the standard curriculum by second or third grade, science fiction "
"stories may well find a home in even younger markets. "

msgid "By the sixth grade, character development becomes important. "
msgstr "By the sixth grade, character development becomes important. "

msgid ""
"Science fiction is often a pleasant and charming way of explaining science "
"or giving facts, but make sure its primary goal is to entertain."
msgstr ""
"Science fiction is often a pleasant and charming way of explaining science "
"or giving facts, but make sure its primary goal is to entertain."

msgid " Romance."
msgstr " Romance."

msgid "Romance stories are popular with sixth graders on up. "
msgstr "Romance stories are popular with sixth graders on up. "

msgid ""
"Contemporary stories often include urban themes such as gangs, alcohol, and "
"sex. "
msgstr ""
"Contemporary stories often include urban themes such as gangs, alcohol, and "
"sex. "

msgid ""
"Today's teens are dealing with some serious situations, and books and "
"stories that accurately reflect their world are popular. "
msgstr ""
"Today's teens are dealing with some serious situations, and books and "
"stories that accurately reflect their world are popular. "

msgid "Nonfiction. "
msgstr "Nonfiction. "

msgid ""
"Nonfiction is popular with readers in the elementary level, and stories in "
"trade books and magazines are often used in the classroom. "
msgstr ""
"Nonfiction is popular with readers in the elementary level, and stories in "
"trade books and magazines are often used in the classroom. "

msgid ""
"Stories about scientific phenomena, the environment, history, and technology"
" interest every age group but the very youngest. "
msgstr ""
"Stories about scientific phenomena, the environment, history, and technology"
" interest every age group but the very youngest. "

msgid ""
"Current events and how-to books are welcome at the elementary and high "
"school level. "
msgstr ""
"Current events and how-to books are welcome at the elementary and high "
"school level. "

msgid "Problem-Oriented Stories. "
msgstr "Problem-Oriented Stories. "

msgid ""
"Issues such as divorce and death (usually the death of a pet) are now being "
"introduced in the first three years instead of, as when this book was first "
"published, the fifth or sixth grade. "
msgstr ""
"Issues such as divorce and death (usually the death of a pet) are now being "
"introduced in the first three years instead of, as when this book was first "
"published, the fifth or sixth grade. "

msgid ""
"These issues must be handled carefully, but they open up new markets for "
"stories that deal with the modern child's reality."
msgstr ""
"These issues must be handled carefully, but they open up new markets for "
"stories that deal with the modern child's reality."

msgid "AGE GROUPS AND READING LEVELSÂ "
msgstr "AGE GROUPS AND READING LEVELSÂ "

msgid ""
"This section covers the age groupings and categories of books that "
"publishers recognize. "
msgstr ""
"This section covers the age groupings and categories of books that "
"publishers recognize. "

msgid "First, let's discuss the age groups.Â "
msgstr "First, let's discuss the age groups.Â "

msgid " Level Books."
msgstr " Level Books."

msgid ""
"Many books are now indicated by levels rather than by specific grades. "
msgstr ""
"Many books are now indicated by levels rather than by specific grades. "

msgid ""
"For example, Level 1 is generally used for kindergarten through second "
"grade. "
msgstr ""
"For example, Level 1 is generally used for kindergarten through second "
"grade. "

msgid ""
"This three-grade spread recognizes that there is a wide range of normal "
"abilities among students. "
msgstr ""
"This three-grade spread recognizes that there is a wide range of normal "
"abilities among students. "

msgid ""
"The vocabulary used for the level is the middle one, in this case, first "
"grade. "
msgstr ""
"The vocabulary used for the level is the middle one, in this case, first "
"grade. "

msgid ""
"Many children are ahead or behind the usual target vocabularies for grade "
"and age, and level books allow the students to use materials that are "
"appropriate for them without some of the social issues involved with reading"
" material identified as being for a grade different from the one the student"
" is in."
msgstr ""
"Many children are ahead or behind the usual target vocabularies for grade "
"and age, and level books allow the students to use materials that are "
"appropriate for them without some of the social issues involved with reading"
" material identified as being for a grade different from the one the student"
" is in."

msgid " Preschool to Kindergarten."
msgstr " Preschool to Kindergarten."

msgid ""
"Preschool books that are self-readers constitute a much larger market than "
"in the past. "
msgstr ""
"Preschool books that are self-readers constitute a much larger market than "
"in the past. "

msgid ""
"Early childhood education is a major focus of both state and national "
"educational programs, and reading is a primary focus. "
msgstr ""
"Early childhood education is a major focus of both state and national "
"educational programs, and reading is a primary focus. "

msgid ""
"Picture books and picture stories are the primary forms for school and home."
" "
msgstr ""
"Picture books and picture stories are the primary forms for school and home."
" "

msgid ""
"As a result, the story that is meant to be read by a caregiver to the child,"
" and is not appropriate as a self-reader as well, has become less common. "
msgstr ""
"As a result, the story that is meant to be read by a caregiver to the child,"
" and is not appropriate as a self-reader as well, has become less common. "

msgid ""
"While the most common sentence length for self-readers at this level is "
"still about six words, some publishers now use longer sentences (up to "
"fifteen words) for even these youngest readers. "
msgstr ""
"While the most common sentence length for self-readers at this level is "
"still about six words, some publishers now use longer sentences (up to "
"fifteen words) for even these youngest readers. "

msgid ""
"To do this, they break the sentences into smaller phrases that generally "
"express a whole idea like the writing sample in the kindergarten section:"
msgstr ""
"To do this, they break the sentences into smaller phrases that generally "
"express a whole idea like the writing sample in the kindergarten section:"

