msgid " The Primary Age Group."
msgstr " The Primary Age Group."

msgid ""
"This group, which includes children from six- to eight-years-old, or first "
"through third grades, reads the picture book, picture story, and easy-to-"
"read book. "
msgstr ""
"This group, which includes children from six- to eight-years-old, or first "
"through third grades, reads the picture book, picture story, and easy-to-"
"read book. "

msgid "More magazines are aimed at this age group than at younger children. "
msgstr "More magazines are aimed at this age group than at younger children. "

msgid ""
"The easy reader is meant for the child to read alone, and the target "
"sentence length is five to six words, ten words maximum. "
msgstr ""
"The easy reader is meant for the child to read alone, and the target "
"sentence length is five to six words, ten words maximum. "

msgid ""
"All the words given in the kindergarten through third-grade word lists are "
"appropriate to use when writing for this group. "
msgstr ""
"All the words given in the kindergarten through third-grade word lists are "
"appropriate to use when writing for this group. "

msgid ""
"There is some movement toward taking the chapter book concept, in very short"
" chapters, to grades one and two rather than waiting until level three or "
"third grade, as is most common."
msgstr ""
"There is some movement toward taking the chapter book concept, in very short"
" chapters, to grades one and two rather than waiting until level three or "
"third grade, as is most common."

msgid " The Elementary Level."
msgstr " The Elementary Level."

msgid ""
"Traditionally this has included the eight- to twelve-year-olds, or the "
"fourth through sixth graders. "
msgstr ""
"Traditionally this has included the eight- to twelve-year-olds, or the "
"fourth through sixth graders. "

msgid ""
"More and more often this now is used to identify third through fifth grade, "
"or seven- through ten- or eleven-year olds. "
msgstr ""
"More and more often this now is used to identify third through fifth grade, "
"or seven- through ten- or eleven-year olds. "

msgid "The target sentence length here is ten words. "
msgstr "The target sentence length here is ten words. "

msgid ""
"The longest length acceptable to conservative institutions is about twenty "
"words. "
msgstr ""
"The longest length acceptable to conservative institutions is about twenty "
"words. "

msgid "Sentence length is more flexible in books than in magazines. "
msgstr "Sentence length is more flexible in books than in magazines. "

msgid ""
"Fiction should have a lot of action, and both fiction and nonfiction should "
"deal with the special interests and problems relevant to this age group. "
msgstr ""
"Fiction should have a lot of action, and both fiction and nonfiction should "
"deal with the special interests and problems relevant to this age group. "

msgid ""
"Most books written for this age group range between 20,000 and 40,000 words."
" "
msgstr ""
"Most books written for this age group range between 20,000 and 40,000 words."
" "

msgid ""
"Most magazines use stories ranging from 700 to 2,000 words and often have a "
"page or two of short-shorts under 100 words."
msgstr ""
"Most magazines use stories ranging from 700 to 2,000 words and often have a "
"page or two of short-shorts under 100 words."

msgid " Middle School Through High School."
msgstr " Middle School Through High School."

msgid ""
"Middle school, a new addition to this book, includes the sixth through "
"eighth grades. "
msgstr ""
"Middle school, a new addition to this book, includes the sixth through "
"eighth grades. "

msgid ""
"The two groups, middle school and high school, include twelve- to eighteen-"
"year-olds. "
msgstr ""
"The two groups, middle school and high school, include twelve- to eighteen-"
"year-olds. "

msgid ""
"Sixth graders, or twelve-year-olds, always constituted a major portion of "
"the readership. "
msgstr ""
"Sixth graders, or twelve-year-olds, always constituted a major portion of "
"the readership. "

msgid "This is the time when reading problems often become serious problems. "
msgstr ""
"This is the time when reading problems often become serious problems. "

msgid ""
"Hi-lo books (for high interest, low reading level) and other materials meant"
" to help the student catch up to grade level are introduced here. "
msgstr ""
"Hi-lo books (for high interest, low reading level) and other materials meant"
" to help the student catch up to grade level are introduced here. "

msgid ""
"Regular texts that are not in the hi-lo grouping use an adult vocabulary and"
" sentence structure. "
msgstr ""
"Regular texts that are not in the hi-lo grouping use an adult vocabulary and"
" sentence structure. "

msgid ""
"Most books range from 25,000 to 55,000 words, and longer lengths are "
"permissible. "
msgstr ""
"Most books range from 25,000 to 55,000 words, and longer lengths are "
"permissible. "

msgid ""
"Popular fiction subjects include romance, mystery, suspense (mild horror), "
"the supernatural, and humor. "
msgstr ""
"Popular fiction subjects include romance, mystery, suspense (mild horror), "
"the supernatural, and humor. "

msgid "More magazines are aimed at this age group than at any other. "
msgstr "More magazines are aimed at this age group than at any other. "

msgid "Magazine stories range from 1,000 to 3,500 words. "
msgstr "Magazine stories range from 1,000 to 3,500 words. "

msgid ""
"Eighty percent of this market is nonfiction and include age-related "
"problems, interviews, and special interests."
msgstr ""
"Eighty percent of this market is nonfiction and include age-related "
"problems, interviews, and special interests."

msgid "WHAT KIND OF BOOK IS IT?"
msgstr "WHAT KIND OF BOOK IS IT?"

msgid ""
"The terms that follow are commonly used by publishers to describe the "
"different types of children's books.Â "
msgstr ""
"The terms that follow are commonly used by publishers to describe the "
"different types of children's books.Â "

msgid " Picture Books."
msgstr " Picture Books."

msgid "There are basically three types of picture books. "
msgstr "There are basically three types of picture books. "

msgid ""
"The first type of picture book is for babies to three-year-olds, has little "
"text, and is often prepared by publishers in-house. "
msgstr ""
"The first type of picture book is for babies to three-year-olds, has little "
"text, and is often prepared by publishers in-house. "

msgid "The next type is for toddlers to five-year-olds. "
msgstr "The next type is for toddlers to five-year-olds. "

msgid ""
"The picture books must be kept short enough to be read aloud by an adult to "
"a child at one sitting. "
msgstr ""
"The picture books must be kept short enough to be read aloud by an adult to "
"a child at one sitting. "

msgid ""
"They should have a happy ending and must use language that can be read aloud"
" comfortably. "
msgstr ""
"They should have a happy ending and must use language that can be read aloud"
" comfortably. "

msgid "Sentence length should also be determined by reading ease. "
msgstr "Sentence length should also be determined by reading ease. "

msgid ""
"If the book is meant to be an early self-reader, the target sentence length "
"should be five to six words, and each page should lend itself to "
"illustration that will help carry the story. "
msgstr ""
"If the book is meant to be an early self-reader, the target sentence length "
"should be five to six words, and each page should lend itself to "
"illustration that will help carry the story. "

msgid "Try to use mainly kindergarten and first-grade vocabulary. "
msgstr "Try to use mainly kindergarten and first-grade vocabulary. "

msgid "These books should take no more than twenty minutes to read."
msgstr "These books should take no more than twenty minutes to read."

msgid ""
"The oldest group of picture book readers is for the five- to eight-year-"
"olds. "
msgstr ""
"The oldest group of picture book readers is for the five- to eight-year-"
"olds. "

msgid "These books must have a story to tell. "
msgstr "These books must have a story to tell. "

